Package: alabaster.files
Title: Wrappers to Save Common File Formats
Version: 1.2.0
Date: 2023-12-30
Authors@R: person("Aaron", "Lun", role=c("aut", "cre"), email="infinite.monkeys.with.keyboards@gmail.com")
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Description: 
    Save common bioinformatics file formats within the alabaster framework.
    This includes BAM, BED, VCF, bigWig, bigBed, FASTQ, FASTA and so on.
    We save and load additional metadata for each file,
    and we support linkage between each file and its corresponding index.
Depends:
    alabaster.base,
Imports:
    methods,
    S4Vectors,
    BiocGenerics,
    Rsamtools
Suggests:
    BiocStyle,
    rmarkdown,
    knitr,
    testthat,
    VariantAnnotation,
    rtracklayer,
    Biostrings
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
biocViews:
    DataRepresentation,
    DataImport
